author: COMSOL
description: This example illustrates the modeling of noise radiation from a gear train housing. A transient analysis is performed to compute the housing vibrations for the specified driver shaft speed. The normal acceleration of the housing obtained is converted to the frequency domain and used as a source of noise. An acoustics analysis is then performed at a selected frequency and sound pressure levels are computed in the near, far, and exterior fields.
